  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Voices from the Territories - Developing New Authentic Narratives to Foster Greater Co-Responsibility in the Implementation of the Peace Agreement</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to ensure that the territories where Development Plans with a Territorial Focus (PDET in Spanish) are being implemented in Colombia have new active and empowered representatives that can increase visibility on the progress and challenges in the implementation of the Peace Agreement.  The project also seeks to promote leadership of peacebuilding and territorial transformation, including advocating for the implementation of gender and ethnic measures in the Agreement. The project aims to strengthen the human and technical capacities in the area of communications of women and youth, including with a gender and ethnic approach involving LGBTIQ+ populations; create access to broad and truthful information on the progress and challenges in the implementation of the Agreement; and support in the identification and execution of initiatives and/or sustainable projects in the area of communication with a territorial approach, with special emphasis on the gender measures of the Peace Agreement. This is done in order to create bonds of trust to motivate actions regarding co-responsibility in the implementation of the Agreement, strengthen trust between communities and institutions, and inspire other territories and society to commit to and encourage contributions to peacebuilding.</narrative>
  </description>
